The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Saregama earnings up 70%

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 29: Saregama India Ltd, the RPG group company, has reported a 70 per cent growth in profit after tax at Rs 8.87 crore in 2005-06 compared with Rs 5.21 crore in the previous year.

 The companys topline grew only by 18 per cent at Rs 118.87 crore against Rs 100.87 crore in 2004-05.

 Saregama performed well in all its businesses during the period. The company had adopted a strategy to focus on the growing opportunities in the audio business in emerging areas of new technological platforms like cell phones, Internet, radio and exploitation of content through publishing.

 At the same time, it continued to strengthen its network to meet emerging opportunities in the retail arena for CDs and music cassettes.

 Saregamas business with five major international studios resulted in significant growth in sales through innovative marketing of home videos and DVDs. 




